6: Ahaha! Now that was a flippin' blast!
9:
Being a troubleshooter ain't half
bad! What do you think, Czarina?
13:
Well, I will admit I like the flashiness
of it.
16:
But I gotta say, it's missing
something... Like a big boat and a
crew.
19: Yeah, I figured you'd say that.
26:
I want a ship! Something fast and
strong—one that only Qualia City
could make!
31: Well, this came out of nowhere...
35:
Amelia's been hanging out in your
world a lot recently, and I've gone
with her a few times...
38:
But kicking butt just doesn't feel the
same without a ship under me.
Guess that's the pirate in me.
42:
I hope you aren't expecting to use
my services free of charge.
46:
Of course not! I can't pay you in your
currency, but I've got plenty of
off-world treasures to cover the
costs.
50:
While I don't mind taking in objects
with no verifiable history... It is going
to cost you.
54:
Is it now? Then how about we get
that King Johnny What's-His-Face to
do the conversion?
62:
All right. I'll even give you a bargain
on the price. Now... what sort of ship
were you thinking?
66:
Well, I want it to fly and be big
enough to live on. Oh, and it's gotta
be strong. And capable of space
travel.
70:
Are you a child?! What comic book
nonsense are you spewing?
74:
Aw come on, you're telling me you
don't hear the same kind of talk
from troubleshooters? What about
that partner of yours?
77:
"This freedom blaster's locked and
loaded!" Man, that's cool. Think she'd
let me use that too?
81:
Of course not. Doing so would be
copyright infringement.
85:
Yarrr, the laws of you landlubbers
matter not on the seven seas!
89:
Oh for—if you're just going to talk
nonsense, this discussion is over.
93:
Ahaha, my bad. Joking aside, is
building a ship like that possible?
97:
Designing and manufacturing
shouldn't be a problem. The issue
stems from a lack of power to run
such a vessel.
100:
So no engine you've got will do the
job, huh? Kinda surprising for such a
futuristic world...
103:
Then what if we leave behind the
sci-fi and head into the world of
fantasy instead?
107:
I've got juuust the power source in
mind—an ancient one, at that.
117: It is a tad small, but I will manage.
121: Awesome! He says he's good to go!
126:
Okay, Lucia, we just need your
biometric authentication right here.
129:
A-all right... Are you sure about this,
Lord Schult?
132:
I am. No one could represent me
better than you.
135:
B-but they're treating you like
luggage!
138:
That is fine. I have... wanted to work
for some time now.
140: As you have all done for me...
149:
Hehe, looks like we're ready to take
this baby for a test drive!
153:
I got a new outfit, just for the
occasion.
158:
Omigoooosh! Czarina, WHERE did
you get that outfit?! So cool! So chic!
SO HOT!
173:
That does it. I can't hold back
anymore! Marinaaa, go on a date
with meee!
182:
Idiot! Didn't we all pledge to see the
cap'n as our leader, not a woman?!
186:
But why's that only apply to me?!
You two are always talkin' about
wantin' to marry her!
191:
Do you WANT to start a ship-wide
fight?!
196: Yeah, it'll be a full-fledged war.
201:
Then I've already won. We already
bathe together.
222:
All right, you scallywags! To your
stations!
227:
Sky Destroyer Schult... Prepare for
take off!
238: At last... I am no longer a NEET.
